Class EmptyTree<K extends java.lang.Comparable<K>,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • tree.EmptyTree<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Tree<K,V>

    public class EmptyTree<K extends java.lang.Comparable<K>,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Tree<K,V>
    This class is used to represent the empty search tree: a search tree that contains no entries. This class is a singleton class: since all empty search trees are the same, there is no need for multiple instances of this class. Instead, a single instance of the class is created and made available through the static field SINGLETON. The constructor is private, preventing other code from mistakenly creating additional instances of the class.
